lombok.experimental

Annotation Type VisitableRoot


  • @Target(value=TYPE)
 @Retention(value=SOURCE)
public @interface VisitableRoot
    Makes a class or interface the root of a visitor design pattern hierarchy. Example: 
      @VisitableRoot
        abstract class RootClass {
  }
    will become: 
      @VisitableRoot
        class RootClass {
    @Override
          public abstract <R> R accept(ClassNameVisitor<R> visitor;
  }
    Also creates a corresponding visitor interface via the VisitorProcessor.
    Author:
    Derek
    See Also:
    Visitable, VisitorProcessor
